Package: animatedplyr
Type: Package
Title: Animated Visualizations of 'dplyr' Verbs for Statistics Education
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Immanuel", "Williams", email = "immanuel@example.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Generates interactive HTML/CSS/JS animations that show how
    'dplyr' verbs (filter, select, mutate) transform a data frame.
    Designed for statistics education: animations render inline below
    Quarto/R Markdown chunks and in the RStudio/Positron Viewer pane.
    Smart sampling keeps displays small (at most 5 rows and 4 columns)
    while preserving the pedagogical signal of each verb. Optional GIF
    export is available via suggested packages.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    dplyr,
    htmltools,
    jsonlite,
    rlang
Suggests:
    knitr,
    magick,
    palmerpenguins,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    webshot2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
LazyData: true
Config/testthat/edition: 3
